  "text": "The Kubernetes scheduler framework defines nine main plugin extension points as Go interfaces in pkg/scheduler/framework/interface.go:\n\n1. **PreFilter** (line 512): Interface for PreFilterPlugin that is called at the beginning of the scheduling cycle to pre-process pod information. Plugins can return a PreFilterResult to filter node candidates and may implement PreFilterExtensions for incremental updates.\n\n2. **Filter** (line 540): Interface for FilterPlugin called during the filtering phase to determine which nodes can run the pod. Also known historically as 'predicates'.\n\n3. **PostFilter** (line 561): Interface for PostFilterPlugin called when scheduling fails at PreFilter or Filter to attempt recovery through preemption or other recovery mechanisms.\n\n4. **PreScore** (line 587): Interface for PreScorePlugin called after filtering phase to prepare scoring data. Allows plugins to generate logs/metrics before actual scoring.\n\n5. **Score** (line 607): Interface for ScorePlugin called on each filtered node to rank them. Plugins can optionally implement ScoreExtensions for normalization of scores.\n\n6. **Reserve** (line 624): Interface for ReservePlugin with Reserve and Unreserve methods to update plugin state when pods are tentatively assigned to nodes (historically called 'assume').\n\n7. **Permit** (line 660): Interface for PermitPlugin called before binding to prevent or delay binding of pods. Can return Success, Wait with timeout, or rejection.\n\n8. **PreBind** (line 640): Interface for PreBindPlugin called before a pod is bound to perform final pre-binding checks.\n\n9. **Bind** (line 673): Interface for BindPlugin called to actually bind a pod to a node. Multiple bind plugins are called in order until one handles the binding.\n\n10. **PostBind** (line 649): Interface for PostBindPlugin called after successful binding for cleanup and informational purposes.\n\nAll these extension point interfaces extend the base **Plugin** interface (line 443) which requires a Name() method.\n\n**Supporting Interfaces:**\n- **PreFilterExtensions** (line 501): Optional interface for PreFilter plugins to provide AddPod and RemovePod methods for incremental updates.\n- **ScoreExtensions** (line 598): Optional interface for Score plugins to provide NormalizeScore method.\n- **EnqueueExtensions** (line 482): Optional interface for plugins that can be unschedulable (PreEnqueue, PreFilter, Filter, Reserve, Permit) to register cluster events that should trigger pod re-queueing.\n- **Framework** (line 686): Main interface that manages plugins and provides methods to run each plugin type.\n- **Handle** (line 783): Interface providing plugins with access to framework internals.\n\n**Implementation and Registration:**\nThe framework implementation is in pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go where the **frameworkImpl** struct maintains slices of each plugin type (preFilterPlugins, filterPlugins, etc.) and the **getExtensionPoints** method (lines 105-117) maps configuration to these plugin slices.\n\nPlugin registration occurs in two places:\n1. pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/registry.go defines the **Registry** type and **PluginFactory** function type for plugin instantiation.\n2. pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/registry.go contains **NewInTreeRegistry** which registers all built-in plugins including DefaultBinder, DefaultPreemption, DynamicResources, ImageLocality, InterPodAffinity, NodeAffinity, NodeName, NodePorts, NodeResources (Fit and BalancedAllocation), NodeUnschedulable, NodeVolumeLimits, PodTopologySpread, QueueSort, SchedulingGates, TaintToleration, VolumeBinding, VolumeRestrictions, and VolumeZone.\n\nPlugin execution is managed through Run* methods in frameworkImpl:\n- RunPreFilterPlugins, RunFilterPlugins, RunPostFilterPlugins, RunPreScorePlugins, RunScorePlugins, RunReservePluginsReserve, RunPermitPlugins, RunPreBindPlugins, RunBindPlugins, RunPostBindPlugins\n\n**Instrumentation:**\npkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/instrumented_plugins.go provides instrumented wrapper implementations for PreFilter, Filter, PreScore, and Score plugins to track metrics while delegating to the actual plugin implementations."
